<HEADLINE> S. African Population Over 40 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 20 (Xinhua) -- South Africa revised its
final results of the 1996 census Tuesday, putting the population
at 40.58 million.
</P>
<P>
In its preliminary census results released last year,
Statistics South Africa said the country had 37.9 million people.
</P>
<P>
Statistics South Africa chief Mark Orkin told reporters in
Pretoria that the revision became necessary after post census
research found that millions of South African had not been
counted during the Census '96, which started in October of that
year.
</P>
<P>
"In our preliminary estimates, the undercount relied solely on
the reports of the respondents," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our follow-up determined that rural respondents, mostly
larger families with less education and more mobility due to
migrant labor, tended to under-report people who might have been
absent during the census."
</P>
<P>
Orkin expressed belief that the latest census was relatively
accurate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
