<HEADLINE> U.N. Marks World Food Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations on
Tuesday observed the World Food Day at its headquarters here.
</P>
<P>
Speakers include President of the General Assembly Didier
Opertti and Deputy Secretary-General Louise Frechette, who is
delivering a keynote speech on behalf of Secretary-General Kofi
Annan.
</P>
<P>
In his message for the World Food Day, which falls on October
16 every year, Annan said, "Every year, World Food Day reminds us
of a tragic reality -- that the war against hunger is still being
fought."
</P>
<P>
The theme for this year's World Food Day is "Women feed the
world."  
</P>
</TEXT>
