<HEADLINE> U.S. Denies Having Any Military Bases in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. embassy in Yemen Tuesday
refuted the allegation that there are U.S. navy bases in Yemen's
Aden province, pointing out the U.S. does not want any military
bases in Yemen.
</P>
<P>
Rumours have it that there is a U.S. State Department document
circulating in Sanaa which mentions the existence of U.S. bases in
Yemen.
</P>
<P>
An embassy statement said some people have forged such a
document in a bid to damage the U.S.-Yemen relations.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Yemen share friendly ties and Washington supports
Yemen's democratization efforts through assistance, as well as
bilateral military cooperation program including now-and-then
visits by U.S. ships to Yemeni ports and joint exercises, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that there is a U.S.-Yemeni agreement on
Yemen's providing its navy facilities on Socatra island in Aden
Gulf for the U.S.. But both countries have denied such an
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
