<HEADLINE> U.N. to Organize U.N. Week in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations will
organize next Saturday a week of activities here aimed at getting
people acquainted with the U.N. bodies in the fields of
maintaining peace, boosting development and preserving heritage, a
U.N. official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy representative of the U.N. Development Program in
Kuwait Nevin Girgis told a news conference that the event, to be
held on the occasion of the United Nations' 53rd anniversary,
will be titled as "Kuwait: Prosperity and Peace" Week.
</P>
<P>
Girgis said that the activities would begin by a speech by
Kuwaiti Information Minister Yousef Al-Sumait and the
inauguration of the Kuwaiti artists exhibition.
</P>
<P>
She said that the exhibition would include a handful of
posters illustrating the U.N. activities in the fields of
development, culture, economy and environment.
</P>
<P>
Part of the exhibition's revenues will be allocated for
assessing children with special needs in hospitals, Girgis said.
</P>
<P>
The official said that three seminars would be held during the
event over "Challenges and Opportunities of Human Development in
Kuwait," "Cooperation among Production Partners for Social
Justice and Economic Prosperity" and "The U.N. Higher Commission
for Refugees -- a Humanitarian Mission."
</P>
<P>
Girgis said that the seminars will be held in cooperation with
Kuwait University and other Kuwaiti institutions.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Iraq-Kuwait Observation Mission (UNIKOM)
would take part in the event by delivering general information
over its peace missions, she said.
</P>
<P>
The UNIKOM was established in 1991 with the mission of
maintaining peace between Iraq and Kuwait after the 1991 Gulf
War. 
</P>
</TEXT>
