<HEADLINE> France to Send Investigation Team to Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 20 (Xinhua) -- France will send an investigation
team to Kosovo this week to assess the actual needs of refugees
for humanitarian aid, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The international community should immediately offer
humanitarian aids to scores of Kosovo refugees, who are now in an
austere situation, to help improve their living conditions and to
insure their personal safety when they return to their homes, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The investigation team will also go to Montenegro, where
refugees are gathering, to do an on-the-spot investigation, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine, also chairman of
the Contact Group on Yugoslav Issues, discussed his views on
sending the team to Kosovo with Kofi Annan, the
U.N. General-Secretary; Javier Solana, NATO General-Secretary, and
Bromislaw Geremek, the current chairman of the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
