<HEADLINE> Consultative Meeting on Somalia Held in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The Second International
Consultative Meeting on Somalia was held here Tuesday in a bid to
facilitate an enabling atmosphere for peace efforts in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the half-day meeting, an International Standing
Committee on Somalia was set up to solicit funds necessary for
the implementation of the peace process and seek international
support for the cause, the Ethiopia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Ethiopian Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs
Tekeda Alemu as saying that the path in the search for peace in
Somalia over the past seven years was "littered with
disappointments and missed opportunities."
</P>
<P>
Tekeda said the objective of this consultation is
to search ways and means of strengthening the internally existing
possibilities for peace and authority formation in Somalia and to
enhance mutual confidence and trust among external parties
committed to peace making in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The first consultative meeting on Somalia was held last March
in Djibouti during the summit of the Inter-Governmental Authority
on Development (IGAD).
</P>
<P>
This meeting was attended by representatives of 36 embassies
in Addis Ababa and various international organizations.  
</P>
