<HEADLINE> Zambia Deports 17 Prohibited Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian Immigration Department
said here Tuesday that it has deported 17 prohibited immigrants
including a German national from Zambia.
</P>
<P>
One Zambian and a Congolese (K) national were also arrested at
the Lusaka International Airport after they tried to travel to
the U.S. on forged Zambian passports.
</P>
<P>
Immigration public relations officer Catherine Poso also told
Zambia News Agency ZANA that another person is being held after
he was found in possession of blank certificates of status for
residence in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Poso said the three men were arrested Monday in Lusaka and
investigations are going on to establish the source of their
documents.
</P>
<P>
She noted that there is need to establish whether the
certificates of status found on the third man were stolen from a
government institution or they were printed by him.
</P>
<P>
The public relations officer added that the 17 people deported
last week mainly come from neighboring countries and west Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Immigration Department is now facing financial constraints
which is hampering the repatriation of prohibited immigrants to
their countries of origin, said Poso.
</P>
<P>
She appealed to human rights and non-governmental
organisations as well as embassies in Zambia to help in terms of
air tickets to ensure illegal immigrants especially from distant
countries are sent back. 
</P>
