U.S. President Bill Clinton to join the summit to use his good
offices with both sides to ensure that the summit will succeed in
reaching a comprehensive agreement.
</P>
<P>
Weizman said that he has been keeping contacts with Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat to ensure that a comprehensive agreement rather than a
partial one will be achieved.
</P>
<P>
Both Hassan and Weizman affirmed that a comprehensive
agreement is necessary because it will bring durable peace to
the region and avoid violence.
</P>
<P>
The Wye Plantation summit entered its sixth day on Tuesday
while Arafat and Netanyahu still could not bridge their gap over
some major issues.
</P>
<P>
The summit was proposed by the U.S. who pins high hopes on the
Palestinians and Israel to reach a comprehensive agreement over
its proposal to reactivate the Palestinian-Israeli peace process
which has been deadlocked since March 1997. 
