<HEADLINE> Two Killed, 20 Injured in Xinjiang Train-Bus Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, October 21 (Xinhua) -- A collision between a cargo
train and a passenger bus on Tuesday night left two deaths and 20
injured in Korla City, in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, according local official reports.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place at the city's North Railway Station at
23:47, when the train collided head-on with the bus which was
heading for Urumqi, the regional capital, from Xinhe County.
</P>
<P>
The pit of bus was completed destroyed, while the first car of
the train was derailed.
</P>
<P>
A rescue team from a local army hospital rushed to the site
shortly after the mishap occurred. Up to now, 17 of the 20 wounded
have been out of danger, with the rest three still under emergency
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
