<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- D.C. United midfielder Ben
Olsen, who left the University of Virginia to join Major League
Soccer's developmental program, was named the U.S.league's rookie
of the year.
</P>
<P>
In a vote of MLS's coaches and general managers, Olsen was
chosen over two other finalists. The 21-year-old played 31 of 32
regular season games, starting 24.
</P>
<P>
