</P>
<P>
-- Syria on Tuesday pledged to shut down camps of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) on its territory and in the
Syrian-controlled Bekka Valley in Lebanon after a two-day meeting
with Ankara held near southern Turkish city of Adana.
</P>
