<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Apparel Textiles Show Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 400 exhibitors from
25 countries and regions are showing their latest collections of
apparel textiles and accessories at Interstoff Asia Autumn 1998.
</P>
<P>
The three-day show at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center is a platform for trading companies, manufacturers, agents,
buying offices, designers and press from around 80 countries and
regions to gain a general overview of the market, to gather
information on fashion trends, to make new contacts and make
orders.
</P>
<P>
Interstoff Asia is the international marketing event in the
Asia-Pacific region for apparel textile products and services. The
fair, organized by international trade fair organizer Messe
Frankfurt, is in its 12th year.
</P>
<P>
One third of exhibitors are from Europe, America and Australia,
with two thirds from Asian countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
On the products side, 19 product groups are represented, with
knitted fabrics ahead of woven fabrics and cotton fabrics just
ahead of fabrics produced from man-made fiber.
</P>
<P>
Leading a new trend this year is the product group "functional
fabrics", which are best known in conjunction with such
applications as in activewear garments for high-performance sports
or for protective clothing for hazardous work environments.
</P>
<P>
Functionality will be a central theme catwalk trend show
presented by Austria-based fiber manufacturer Lenzing.
</P>
<P>
Interstoff Asia and the related Trend Forum provide, at a time
for the transition into the 21st century, essential information
for trade visitors looking ahead to the feel for the coming
season, and the first impressions of the new millennium around the
corner. Some experts had already picked up "Contemporary",
"Leisure Time" and "Future" as the three themes which will embody
a balance of such factors as the complex mix of social relations,
daily needs, materials, colors, feelings and time which influence
consumers and form the fashion outlook for Autumn-Winter
1999/2000.
</P>
<P>
The visitors will get a bonus as well since they could visit
the neighboring International Trade Fair for Yarns and Fibers or
Interyarn, with over 20 exhibitors from eight countries and
regions taking part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
