and professionally," he said in a bank's news release, without
explaining why. (US-Bank President-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli news media said on Wednesday that Israeli
and Palestinian negotiators, who are holding talks at the
seclusive Wye Plantation outside Washington, will reach a peace
deal soon.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post newspaper quoted a senior member of the
Israeli delegation as saying that the bargaining is "gruesome,"
but "there is a good chance we will clinch a deal at the last
minute."
</P>
<P>
Local daily Haaretz said sources from all three sides
concurred that after five days of deadlock, the mood turned
upbeat on Tuesday and an agreement might be finalized on
Wednesday or Thursday. (Israel-Palestine-Talks)
</P>
