- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- The former boss of South Korean Kia Group, Kim
Sun-hong, was sentenced to seven years in prison Wednesday for
embezzling company funds and guaranteeing debts for insolvent
subsidiaries, which led to the group's bankruptcy.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who headed Kia until last October, was convicted of
illegally ordering the group's flagship, Kia Motors, to lend 1.1
trillion won (some 1.1 billion U.S. dollars at the time) to four
troubled subsidiaries and guarantee 2.8 trillion won (2.8 billion
dollars) in debts incurred by them. (SKorea-Boss-Punishment)
