<HEADLINE> Promotions for '99 Kunming Int'l Horticultural Expo Hosted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- A week of promotional
activities for the '99 Kunming International Horticultural
Exposition, which will take place from May 1 to October 1, 1999,
in Kunming, capital city of Yunnan Province, began here today.
</P>
<P>
The activities include a report on the work of preparations for the
exposition, a fair to mark the event in Zhongshan Park, open-air
photo exhibitions and ethnic dress shows, and performances by ethnic
artists from the southwest China province.
</P>
<P>
Xu Rongkai, deputy secretary general of the State Council, said
in the report on preparations given this afternoon at the Great
Hall of People that the 184-day exposition will be jointly
sponsored by the Chinese government and the Yunnan provincial
government. This will be the foremost international exposition
ever hosted by the Chinese government, and also the last grand
world fair this century.
</P>
<P>
Xu, also vice chairman of the '99 Kunming Expo Organizing
Committee, said that with the theme "Man and Nature -- Marching
into 21st Century." the exposition will play a positive role in
developing China's opening up to the rest of the world, promoting
the tourism industry, improving environmental technology and
enhancing the country's international status.
</P>
<P>
Li Jiating, governor of Yunnan Province, said that about 85
percent of the construction of the major exhibition halls and
centers for the event has been completed, including the
12,000-square meter international hall, the 17,000-square meter
Chinese hall, and a 3,400-square meter greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
"Some 58 countries and 18 international organizations have so
far signed participation contracts, among which are many developed
countries with unique horticultural characteristics," Li added.
</P>
</TEXT>
