<HEADLINE> Science and Technology Fair Opens in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 21 (Xinhua) -- A science and technology fair
opened in the north China port city of Tianjin today, attended by
representatives from 25 northern Chinese cities around the Bohai
Sea.
</P>
<P>
Some 350 scientific research institutes, universities and
high-tech enterprises participated in the "'98 China Bohai
Sea-Rim Science and Technology Fair" today, including Beijing
University, Qinghua University, and the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The participants exhibited their latest products and inventions
in traditional sectors like chemicals, metallurgical and
construction materials, and in innovative fields such as new
materials, new energy sources, bio-engineering, information
technology, environmental protection, and agriculture. 
</P>
