<HEADLINE> Regional Consultative Meeting to Be Held in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The fourth consultative
meeting of the heads of the sub-regional organizations in Asia and
the Pacific and the Economic and Social Commission for Asia and
the Pacific (ESCAP) will be held here on October 26-27.
</P>
<P>
The seven-nation South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) will host the meeting at the Kathmandu-based
SAARC Secretariat, the secretariat said in a press release
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the first of its nature to be held in Kathmandu,
will be attended by heads of the ESCAP, the Economic Cooperation
Organization, the Association of Southeast Asian Nations and the
Forum, the secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
High-level representatives from the United Nations Development
Program and the Asian Development Bank are also expected at the
meeting, it said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the meeting is annually held for high-level
consultations aimed at strengthening cooperation among these
organizations in the vital areas of trade, investment, development
of infrastructure, poverty eradication, human resource development
and greater people-to-people contact.
</P>
<P>
The fourth meeting is expected to consider concrete modalities
for further strengthening cooperation among the organizations with
a view to addressing the challenges faced by countries in the
region in sustaining the momentum of development and enhancing the
contributory role of sub-regional organizations in the process.
</P>
<P>
It is also expected to consider several ideas about
significantly promoting cooperation among sub-regional
organizations to enhance their institutional capabilities to
effectively address the new challenges to constructive regionalism
arising from the present global economic uncertainties.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the meeting will explore specific ways for
strengthening cooperation among the sub-regional organizations in
the region and specialized U.N. agencies and other international
bodies, the secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala is scheduled to
inaugurate the meeting on October 26, which will be chaired by
SAARC Secretary-General Naeem U. Hasan, it added.
</P>
<P>
The consultative meeting was last held in Tehran, Iran, in May
1997.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC now groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
