<HEADLINE> EU Seeks Better WTO Dispute Settlement System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 21 (xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
proposed to raise the transparency and efficiency of the dispute
settlement procedures in the World Trade Organization (WTO), a
news release from the EU headquarters said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The EU submitted a total of 24 suggestions, the major of which
included creating a standing body of professional panelists,
improving transparency, giving greater weight to consultations,
and speeding up procedures.
</P>
<P>
In its proposal, which forms part of a general review of the
dispute settlement system currently taking place in Geneva, the EU
mainly stressed the importance of improving transparency in the
WTO system.
</P>
<P>
The EU believes greater transparency is essential in
making dispute settlement rulings more acceptable to the general
public.
</P>
<P>
The proposal said the need for transparency increased in recent
years, as the WTO rulings touched on sensitive issues, such as the
public health and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The EU also wants the WTO rulings to be made available faster to
the public in the three official WTO languages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
