<HEADLINE> S'pore Armed Forces Conducting Exercise in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Armed forces (SAF)
is staging an armored and live firing exercise at Shoalwater Bay
Training Area in Australia, the Ministry for Defense of Singapore
announced in a press release Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,200 personnel from the Armor and Guards battalions
are involved in the exercise, codenamed Exercise Wallaroo 98,
which lasts for 45 days from October 1, 1998 to November 14 1998.
</P>
<P>
Live firing exercise, Armor Battle Group maneuvers and
helicopter-borne training are listed on the agenda of the
exercise, the fourth in the Wallaroo series which started in 1994.
</P>
<P>
A Super Puma helicopter detachment from the Republic of
Singapore Air Force, stationed at the Australian Army Aviation
Center in Oakey, is providing support to the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Defense said exercises like Wallaroo allow the
SAF to conduct large-scale training in a realistic environment,
which it is unable to do in Singapore, given the shortage of land
and airspace.
</P>
<P>
The three services of the SAF often take part in exercises held
in overseas lands and waters to enhance their combat capability.
</P>
</TEXT>
