<HEADLINE> Typhoon Slams Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Babs (locally named
Loleng) stroke the central Philippines Wednesday, the Philippine
Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Service Administration
(PAGASA) said.
</P>
<P>
It was the ninth typhoon to hit the Philippines this year.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon, with center winds of from 140 kilometers to 235
kilometers per hour, lashed Bicol and other areas in the central
Philippines, leaving many areas flooded and brought the traffic in
these areas to standstill, PAGASA said.
</P>
<P>
It said that residents in low-lying areas have evacuated to
safe grounds and were advised not to venture out into the sea.
</P>
<P>
It added that the typhoon is expected to weaken after crossing
Catanduanes province Wednesday evening and continuing moving
northeast to Polilio island.
</P>
<P>
Public storm warning signal number one is in effect over Luzon,
including Metro Manila where drizzle was brought by the typhoon,
it said.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Babs is mild when compared with supertyphoon Zab which
crossed the country on October 14-15, leaving 86 people dead and a
heavy financial loss of one billion pesos (23 million U.S.
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
