<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Launches Massive Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- China expects to complete
construction of nearly 49 million square meters of affordable
housing this year by spending 41.9 billion yuan, as the demand for
housing continues to expand.
</P>
<P>
According to Ye Rutang, vice minister of Construction, new
housing reform policies are being carried out nationwide and are
enjoying the full support of the people.
</P>
<P>
Under the new housing reform plan, China will cancel
welfare-based housing allocations step by step and promote
the commercialization of housing.
</P>
<P>
New and affordable housing will be sold to workers and staff
only, as ever more workers and staff will purchase their own
apartments by using housing subsidies, public housing funds and
bank loans, said the senior official.
</P>
<P>
In line with housing reform, commercial banks have begun to
provide mortgages for private housing purchases, and a public
housing fund-raising system has been instituted which is expected
to sharply stimulate housing purchases nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide demand for housing keeps rising, the
vice-minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
To increase the average per capita urban living space to 9
square meters by the end of the century, the country must build
175 million square meters of affordable housing each year, and
renovate or rebuild 200 million square meters of existing housing
annually.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, housing reform is meant to bring
a rational and stable development to the real estate sector, which
now consists mainly of affordable housing projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
