<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK and Belgium, Israel Agree to Avoid Double Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has reached
agreements separately with Belgium and Israel on arrangements to
provide double taxation relief for airline income.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said here Wednesday Hong Kong has signed
Air Services Agreements respectively with Belgium and Israel. Both
agreements have contained a double taxation relief article on
airline income.
</P>
<P>
Under the arrangements, Hong Kong will tax the income generated
from international traffic of Hong Kong airlines derived from
Belgium and Israel and which has been granted full tax relief by
the two countries respectively.
</P>
<P>
In return, Hong Kong will forgo the right to tax the income of
Belgian and Israeli airlines derived from Hong Kong if such income
is subject to tax in their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
"It is our policy to include provisions on double taxation
relief for airline income into Air Services Agreements negotiated
between Hong Kong and our bilateral aviation partners," the
spokesman explained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
