<HEADLINE> Roundup: Macao Publicity Week Held in Mainland Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 21 (Xinhua) -- With the latest Macao publicity
week being inaugurated Tuesday in China's northwestern city of
Xi'an, people in the inland areas of China are becoming more
acquainted with Macao which will return to the motherland in
December 1999.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
and Ho Hau Wah, chairman of the executive council of the Macao
Basic Law Promotion Association, were present at the inauguration
ceremony Tuesday morning together with Shaanxi provincial
officials.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, such publicity weeks were held in Beijing, Nanjing
and Fuzhou cities in May, July and August, respectively. The
publicity activities attracted the attention of high-level local
officials and people from all walks of life. It is estimated that
a total of 100,000 people participated in the activities.
</P>
<P>
In addition, news media in the inland areas and those from Hong
Kong and Macao made wide coverage of the publicity weeks.
</P>
<P>
According to sponsors of the publicity weeks, such activities
enabled people in the mainland areas to know more about Macao's
history and the current situation here, and the process and
significance of Macao's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, some of Macao's specialists touring together
the activities said they acquired more knowledge about the
mainland through exchanges with their counterparts in the
mainland.
</P>
<P>
On display during Macao publicity weeks are 60 photos and 70
paintings which depict Macao's natural scenery, folk customs and
urban outlook, and more than 180 drawings which show the
systematic procedure of the settlement of the Macao question and
the Chinese government's basic policy for Macao.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are more than 120 sets of delicate stamps
provided by the Macao Postal and Telecommunications Department,
which depict Macao's unique culture and tourist attractions.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 kinds of books on display also show the booming
publishing business in Macao. In east China's Nanjing city, it is
said, two book specialists pored over the books for an entire
afternoon and said that they had not expected such high-quality
books and so many scholars in Macao are engaged in cultural and
academic studies.
</P>
<P>
The publicity activities are sponsored by the Xinhua News
Agency Macao Branch, the Macao Basic Law Promotion Association,
Macao Daily News, the Macao Association of Chinese Enterprises and
local publicity departments in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the sponsors said that many provinces and
municipalities including Anhui, Zhejiang, Sichuan, Guangdong and
Shanghai, are vying for a Macao publicity week there.
</P>
<P>
It has been decided that similar publicity weeks will be held
in Shijiazhuang in late November, Guangzhou in late December, and
Shanghai early next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
