<HEADLINE> Meeting of Asian Export Credit Agencies Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth Meeting of Asian
Export Credit Agencies sponsored by the China Export and Import
Bank (Eximbank) opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the meeting were representatives from India,
Japan, Australia, Indonesia, the Philippines, Singapore, the
Republic of Korea and China.
</P>
<P>
The main theme of the meeting is exploring ways to utilize
export credit agencies during the current Southeast Asian
financial crisis and national economic restructuring.
</P>
