<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Human Rights Symposium (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xie said each country has its own historical traditions,
cultural backgrounds and social systems, different levels of
development and values. However, it is due to diversification that
the understanding of things by the human race can be enriched and
deepened.
</P>
<P>
He said that international cooperation is an essential means
for promoting human rights worldwide. The United Nations has
established the promotion and protection of human rights as one of
its principal tasks.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Charter clearly stipulates that the
promotion and protection of human rights should be realized
through international cooperation, according to Xie.
</P>
<P>
He added that dialog is the first step towards cooperation and
also an important factor for promoting the cause. Dialog must be
based on equality and mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 papers were presented during the
symposium. Scholars and experts from China and five continents
made enthusiastic speeches to reaffirm the historic position and
role of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights in the cause for
human rights development. They also reviewed the path traveled
thus far and the major achievements in the human rights cause over
the past half century, reflected on the remaining problems and
challenges, looked ahead to human rights in the 21st century, and
expressed their common determination to promote human rights
around the globe.
</P>
<P>
Participants engaged in heated discussions on human rights
issues and expressed their belief that rights to subsistence and
development, as well as the social, economic and cultural and
political rights of citizens are of equal importance.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that developing and developed countries will
be required to make their due contributions to the ensuring of
sustainable development worldwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Hold Four-Nation Men's Volleyball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, Fujian Province, October 21 (Xinhua) -- China will
hold a four-nation men's volleyball tournament to help its
national team prepare for the World Championships and the Asian
Games, it was announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese national team coach Wang Jiawei, the
four teams involving in the tournament will be world champions
Cuba, Canada, Poland and Chinese national team. All the four
teams have already booked their respective berth in the World
Championships.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will adopt a knock-out format with China
playing Poland and Cuba taking Canada on November 5. The winners
of the two matches will vie for the title of the tournament on
November 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
