<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets with Zambian Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Li Peng
said in a meeting with Zambian Defense Minister Chitalu Sampa and
his party that Sino-Zambian relations have been developing well.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China and Zambia have always supported and
cooperated with each other in international affairs, and said that
Sampa's current China visit will serve to develop relations
between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Li highly appreciated the Zambian government's adherence to the
"One China" policy and its support of China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
With regard to China's policy toward Africa, Li said China
hopes that the continent will enjoy a long-standing peaceful
environment, thus creating favorable conditions for economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
China also places great importance on its relations with
Zambia and other African nations, Li said, adding that China
believes Africa is a promising continent.
</P>
<P>
Sampa appreciated China's rapid economic growth, and said he
believes that China will make even greater progress in post-flood
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his country's gratitude for China's support
over the past decades, and reiterated that Zambia will continue to
observe the "One China" policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
