<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Extends Loans of 500 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- In the first nine months of
this year, the China Construction Bank (CCB) extended loans
totalling 528.3 billion yuan, an increase of 79 billion yuan over
last year, sources from CCB said today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that by the end of the third quarter, the CCB's
outstanding loans increased 114.1 billion yuan compared with the
beginning of the year, and ended the quarter at 81.5 percent of
the entire year's target.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the bank said that in the first three quarters
the bank continued to focus its loans on highways, railways,
telecommunications, power grids and urban infrastructure
projects, and further improved financial services for medium and
small enterprises and foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
By the end of September, most of the CCB's promised loans to
highways, railways, telecommunications and other infrastructure
projects had arrived. In October, the bank became the first
to announce that it will commence extending domestic automobile
loans, a move that attracted wide attention.
</P>
<P>
As the largest correspondent bank for the State Development
Bank's (SDB) commission transactions, the CCB has handled payments
of 71.4 billion yuan on behalf of the the SDB in the first nine
months this year, thereby ensuring sufficient capital for the
state's key construction projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
