<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Resource Indonesia 1998" Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie Wednesday urged thousands of Indonesian and foreign
businessmen participating as suppliers and buyers in an
international trade exhibition to make a win-win cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"I hope, and I am sure, that we could make a win-win
cooperation here," the president said while opening the five-day
exhibition "Resource Indonesia 1998" in Central Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Habibie said this year's "Resource Indonesia" is special to the
crisis-hit country because the number of its participants has
reached 825 for Indonesian suppliers and 3,500 for foreign buyers
coming from 76 countries.
</P>
<P>
"I was told that the number of participants is more than
expected. This reflects that confidence in this nation is
returning," he said.
</P>
<P>
This return of international confidence in Indonesia could also
be seen from the strengthening of the rupiah's value against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
He said he took note of reports Wednesday morning that the
rupiah was trading at 7,050 to the greenback, appreciating by
about 40 percent since July.
</P>
<P>
The president further noted that inflation rate by the end of
this month is expected to reach minus 0.75 percent, much lower
than September's 3.7 percent or July's 18.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
This has helped reduce the prices of such basic commodities as
rice and cooking oil, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Habibie reminded the people to continue working hard
to end the country's economic woes.
</P>
<P>
"We should never feel pessimistic in finding a way out of this
crisis. We need to improve the competitiveness of our export
products," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
