<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Hosts Symposium on Protecting Taiwan Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice Minister of Justice Liu
Chang stressed today that judicial departments at all levels
should actively provide legal services and protect the rights
and interests of Taiwan investors according to law.
</P>
<P>
Liu made the remark during a symposium on the theory and
practice of the Law on Protecting the Investments of Taiwan
Compatriots. The symposium opened today in Kunshan, east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 160 staffers from central and provincial Taiwan
affairs departments and representatives for Taiwan investors with
inland ventures attended the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Liu said the goal of the symposium is further perfect the
theory on the aforementioned law, improve legal environment for
Taiwan investments, and protect both their rights and interests.
The goal also includes promoting economic and cross-straits trade
relations and advancing the process of reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The law was adopted on March 5, 1994, during the Sixth Meeting
of the Eighth Standing Committee of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Liu urged judicial departments at all levels to do a good job
in publicizing the law, especially in areas where Taiwan
investments are concentrated.
</P>
<P>
Kunshan, located in southern Jiangsu, is one of the country's
leading regions in terms of concentrated Taiwan investments. The
city has approved 610 Taiwan enterprises involving total
contractual investments of 3.4 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
