<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Prime Minister Visits Suzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, October 21 (Xinhua)-- Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan
Van Khai and his party are visiting the scenic city of Suzhou in
east China's Jiangsu Province today.
</P>
<P>
Acting Governor Ji Yunshi welcomed the Vietnamese delegation
and briefed its members on Jiangsu's history, geology, economic
development, reform and opening efforts, and goals for the future.
</P>
<P>
Ji noted that Jiangsu and Viet Nam have enjoyed close contacts
in the past, and expressed the hope for increased bilateral
exchanges in the future.
</P>
<P>
Phan said Jiangsu, one of China's most developed areas, has
recorded great achievements in industrial and agricultural
production, introduction of overseas investment, and improvement
of local residents' living standards.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Jiangsu and Viet Nam have basically the
same size populations, with the latter enjoying a much higher per
capita income. Phan said the goal of his visit is to promote
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government encourages enterprises from the two
sides to cooperate in areas such as trade and mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
The delegation visited the Suzhou Industrial Park jointly
developed by China and Singapore and the new area of Suzhou in the
afternoon and later travelled to Hangzhou, capital of east China's
Zhejiang Province. 
</P>
