<HEADLINE> Dhaka Approves 13 Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of the
National Economic Council (ECNEC) of Bangladesh Tuesday approved
13 projects to be implemented in various economic sectors,
agriculture, an English daily newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With an outlay of 11.08 billion taka (about 228.5 million U.S.
dollars) including project assistance of 4.48 billion taka (about
92.4 million dollars), the 13 projects will be implemented in
water resource, energy, science and technology, youth and sports,
textile and education sectors, The Independent said.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, who chaired the ECNEC meeting,
called for expediting implementation of the projects to complete
those on time.
</P>
<P>
She also asked for taking appropriate disciplinary actions
against officials found responsible for violating the norms and
procedure of the project implementation.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister announced that the ECNEC meeting will be
held every week in order to further speed up the approval of the
development projects. 
</P>
