<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose a minor
19.37 points, or 0.20 percent, to end at 9,662.12 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip Hang Seng Index opened strongly at 9,790.74, with
a gain of 147.99 points, or 1.53 percent, before hitting the day's
high of 9,894.73 in mid-morning.
</P>
<P>
At lunchbreak the index stood at 9,662.62, edging up 19.87
points, or 0.21 percent.
</P>
<P>
The value of turnover amounted to 7,087 million HK dollars (909
million U.S. dollars), against the previous session's 7,355
million HK dollars (943 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The index rose 43.70 points, or 0.46 percent, to close at
9,642.75 on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
