<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index gained
1.40 points to 424.37, the all-share Emas Index dropped 0.32 of a
point to 111.25, the Industrial Index lost 6.89 points to 821.26
and the Second Board Index shed 1.83 points to 102.84.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 525 to 139 while 132 counters were
unchanged, 120 untraded and 34 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was lower at 290.163 million shares valued
at 445.821 million ringgit (117.321 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 350.688 million shares worth 567.049 million ringgit
(149.223 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover was lower at 273.242 million shares
valued at 420.072 million ringgit (110.545 million U.S. dollars)
from 328.906 million shares worth 531.746 million ringgit (139.933
million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover dropped to 16.921 million shares
valued at 25.748 million ringgit (6.775 million U.S. dollars) from
21.781 million shares worth 35.303 million ringgit (9.29 million
U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover declined to 4.244 million shares valued at
8.791 million ringgit (2.313 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's
7.795 million shares worth 13.306 million ringgit (3.501 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 11.186
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
20.118 million shares, construction 29.089 million shares,
trading/services 73.818 million shares, infrastructure 958,000
shares, finance 51.261 million shares, hotels 903,000 million
shares, properties 48.986 million shares, plantation 5.958 million
shares, mining 1.125 million shares, trusts 122,000 shares,
closed/fund 67,000 shares and loans 29.650 million shares.
</P>
</TEXT>
