<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices gyrated from
negative to positive territory on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday
buoyed by the stronger regional currencies and buying of banking
and property stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) climbed up 32.16 points
to end at 1140.91 points in active buying largely from fund
investors .
</P>
<P>
Dealers said market sentiment was also encouraged by
expectations that Japan may expand its 30 billion U.S. dollar aid
package.
</P>
<P>
They said spillover from the buoyant Japanese stock market was
seen fueling the rise in Singapore bourse.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 656.63 million units valued at
656.63 million Singapore dollars (418.93 million U.S. dollars).
The advancers outnumbered decliners by 292 to 32, more than nine
times, with 95 counters unchanged..
</P>
<P>
Van DH remained the most active units with a volume of 28.39
million shares. It was followed by Frt Links which had a turnover
of 23.80 million units. KepLand was next with 23.37 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DCBC F led the ascent of the day as it rose by 60 cents to 7.20
Singapore dollars at close. RothmansI went up 50 cents to finish
at 8.10 Singapore dollars. ABR Hldgs was up 42 cents to end at
1.65 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sem was the biggest loser of the day
with a drop of 35 cents to close at 8.55 Singapore dollars. ANA Ho
slid 15 cents to close at 1.60 Singapore dollars. Focal shed off
11 cents to end at 1.12 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
