<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Capital to Hold Consumer Goods Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian capital will
hold a consumer goods fair during December 16-23, said a Board of
External Trade (BET) official Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 40 companies from Tanzania, Iran, China, Pakistan
and other countries have confirmed to attend the Third Dar es
Salaam Consumer Fair, said Cleobhas Luhumbika, a senior export
promotion officer with BET.
</P>
<P>
More confirmation is coming, Luhumbika told Xinhua over
telephone.
</P>
<P>
The fair will attract a lot of visitors because it is arranged
at a time before Christmas and New Year, he said, adding that all
kinds of consumer goods will be displayed.
</P>
<P>
BET, the organizer, will charge local exhibitors 10,000
Shillings (about 14.9 U.S. Dollars) for per square meter of
displaying space, while foreign exhibitors are expected to pay 40
U.S. Dollars for the same space, he said. 
