<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Jaffna Appeals for International Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The leaders and members of
local bodies in Sri Lanka's Jaffna city have appealed to the
international community to prevent the Tamil rebels from
disrupting the democratic functions in the north, according to
reports reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A letter to the international community signed by the leaders
and members of all the 17 local bodies in Jaffna city had been
sent to the embassies and high commissions in Colombo and other
foreign non-governmental organizations, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the letter which was delivered Tuesday called
for the immediate involvement of the international community in
halting the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)'s undemocratic
actions in the north.
</P>
<P>
The letter also said that all local bodies were elected in
polls in Jaffna in January this year, but since then two mayors
and several members of the local bodies in Jaffna city have been
assassinated by the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
The Jaffna peninsula was once the stronghold of the LTTE
rebels, who have been waging a 15-year war for a separate state in
the country. Government troops recaptured the peninsula in May
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
