<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Urges S. Asian Experts to Work Together </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina has urged the South Asian scientists, technologists and
engineers to work together in transforming all their innovations
and endeavors into welfare of nearly 1.24 million people in the
region.
</P>
<P>
She made this remark while formally inaugurating the 4-day long
first-ever convention of the SAARC (South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation) Diploma Engineers Forum here Tuesday, a
daily newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
