<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Develop Southern Chinese Province as Ecology Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The island province of Hainan
has followed a road of coordinating economic development with
environmental protection in an attempt to become the country's
No.1 ecology center by the year 2002.
</P>
<P>
The province has been trying to develop environmentally-sound
agriculture, high-yield agriculture, tourism, and fisheries.
</P>
<P>
An industrial layout has been worked out to restrict pollution
in certain areas and environmental protection input has increased,
with infrastructure receiving the most financial support.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government says that by the year 2002, the
province's environmental protection will include forest coverage,
water quality, and air quality, and by 2000, the province will
become the first not to use fluorine in refrigeration, have
industrial pollution discharge standards, ban the use of leaded
gas, and increase the use of new energy instead of coal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
