<HEADLINE> Cyclist Valentino Fois Suspended until April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Cyclist Valentino Fois of Italy
has been suspended until April 1, 1999, by the Court of
Arbitration of Sport in Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The court ruled that a decision by a appeal panel of the
Italian Cycling Federation to treat two separate cases of doping
by Fois as a single case was not correct.
</P>
<P>
The court made the ruling after the international cycling body
UCI appealed in July in order to overturn the Italians' decision.
</P>
<P>
Fois was originally banned for only eight months from
September 30, 1997 but the UCI wanted him suspended for an
additional year.
</P>
<P>
Fois tested positive for performance-enhancing drugs during
the 1997 Tours of Switzerland and Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
