<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Vietnamese Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister
General Chi Haotian met here today with a visiting Vietnamese
delegation led by Lieutenant General Doan Chuong, president of the
Institute of Military Strategy of the Viet Nam Defense Ministry,
and his party.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Doan's visit coincides with a visit by
Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai, said Chi, adding that the
extensive consensus reached between the Vietnamese prime minister
and Chinese premier has laid down a solid foundation for the
further growth of Sino-Vietnamese relations.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of Chinese Central Military Commission
and a state councillor, noted that both countries are facing
problems related to peace and development, and both attach
importance to enhancing their national defense and army
building. He expressed his hope for the further improvement of
friendly cooperative ties between the two countries and their
armies.
</P>
<P>
China has, under the staunch leadership of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, has
not only withstood the adverse affects of the financial crisis
sweeping Southeast Asia, but triumphed over rare flooding in
history, said Chi. He added that the successes testify to China's
growing national strength, as well as the role the People's
Liberation Army's has been playing in protecting the interests of
the nation and its people.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Doan pointed to the traditional friendship
between the two nations and their armies, and expressed the hope
to learn from China's experiences in military affairs research.
</P>
