<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, October 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW -- The Polish government Tuesday unanimously passed a
draft resolution on the country's ratification of the North
Atlantic Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The move has come as an immediate follow-up to Prime Minister
Jerzy Buzek's visit to the headquarters of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO). The document has reportedly been
submitted to the parliament for endorsement. During talks with
NATO Secretary General Javier Solana in Brussels earlier, Buzek
expressed Poland's wish for an early entry into NATO.
(Poland-NATO-Resolution)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Participants in an Italy-Japan Business Group meeting
Tuesday urged Japan to get rid of protectionism and open its
domestic market if it wants to overcome its current economic and
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 10th assembly of the group held here Tuesday,
World Trade Organization (WTO) Director General Renato Ruggiero,
an Italian, observed that protectionism "could turn out to be a
tragic mistake. No nation today can afford to build walls against
investment." (Italy-Japan-Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
QUITO -- Ecuadoran President Jamil Mahuad left for Argentina
and Chile Tuesday to seek support in a long-running border dispute
with Peru.
</P>
<P>
Mahuad said he would seek the support of Presidents Carlos
Menem of Argentina and Eduardo Frei of Chile for his country's
claim on the border dispute. However, Peru's Foreign Minister
Fernando de Trazegnies said in Lima on the same day that Mahuad's
trip would not reverse a decision reportedly made by the four
mediating countries that Peru has the sovereignty over the border
area in dispute. (Ecuador-Peru-Border Dispute)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Vietnam's Communist Party General Secretary Le Kha
Phieu met with Russian Defense Minister Marshal Igor Sergeyev
Tuesday, official newspaper reports here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Sergeyev, who arrived here Tuesday for an
official visit, promised that Russia will "do its utmost to
maintain and boost bilateral ties for mutual interest."
(Vietnam-Russia-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
