<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP Assists Zambia in Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- To help Zambia manage its
environmental degradation, the United Nations Development Program
(UNDP) has provided the east African country with nine vehicles
and some office equipment worth over 310,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
And four$motor cycles were also handed over to the Environment
and Natural Resources Ministry, Times of Zambia said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The gesture is for the country's environment and natural
resources program under a UNDP Environmental Sup|879: Program.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the delivering ceremony here Tuesday, UNDP
resident representative Omeofe Oyaide said it was gratifying that
the program was off to a firm and encouraging start with the
procurement of the vehicles and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Receiving the donation, Jewette Masinja, permanent secretary
of Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources, said that the
objective of the program was to enhance national capacity to
manage the environment and natural resources at the community
level.
</P>
<P>
He praised the program for responding to the overall
government policy of poverty reduction within the work of
economic growth and protection of the environment and natural
eVvironmental degradation.
</P>
<P>
Masinja attributed the environmental degradation in Zambia to
poverty and lack of survival strategies, inadequate understanding
of environmental problems, weak administrative and legal frame
work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
