<HEADLINE> Shanghai Lottery Minting Millionaires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen lucky people have
become millionaires overnight by buying social welfare lottery
tickets for five yuan (0.64 US dollars) in China's largest
industrial and commercial city.
</P>
<P>
The chance of becoming a millionaire is one in a million. The
winners have been from Shanghai and other parts of the
country. They pay 200,000 yuan in taxes from their million yuan in
winnings. Most say they plan to spend the money on improved living
condition like a new house.
</P>
<P>
In fact, according to an official at the lottery center, there
would have been more winners if they had checked their lottery
numbers carefully.
</P>
<P>
The city has sold 260 million yuan worth of lottery tickets
that will add nearly 100 million yuan to the social welfare fund,
the official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
