<HEADLINE> 2 Earthquakes Hit New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Two earthquakes measuring
6.1 and 4.2 on the Richter Scale respectively hit New Zealand
Tuesday and Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Television New Zealand reported that an earthquake,
measuring 6.1 and centered 44 kilometers north of Haast in
central-western South Island, rocked the island around 9:00 a.m.
Wednesday. The quake caused some damage to houses, but no
casualties have been reported.
</P>
<P>
Another earthquake hit the southern part of the North Island at
11:50 p.m. Tuesday, with the epicenter at 3 kilometers west of
Woodville. It was measured 4.2 on the Richter Scale. 
</P>
