<HEADLINE> China Giving Foreign Businesses National Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 21 (Xinhua) -- China will gradually give
foreign-funded enterprises the same treatment as domestic
businesses, Vice-minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Sui Guangxiang said at a trade fair for central and
western regions on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will create an open and orderly competitive
market environment and use foreign funds in a more rational way.
</P>
<P>
Liu Mingkang, a vice-president at the People's Bank of China,
told the gathering that China will open further to foreign
financial institutions in the amount and scale of Chinese currency
dealings.
</P>
<P>
He said that a unified tax rate for both Chinese and
foreign-funded financial institutions and related issues are being
discussed.
</P>
<P>
Local government leaders at the fair also promised to improve
their service and guarantee the rights and interest of investors.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor of Hubei Province Zhang Hongxiang said that
foreign-funded enterprises will not only enjoy the same status as
Chinese counterparts in access to infrastructure but also to food,
medicines, and railway and ship tickets as well. 
