<HEADLINE> India's Luxury Car Sales Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The luxury car segment in
India suffered a drop of over 9 percent in the first half of the
current financial year, 'Business Standard' said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The total luxury car sales in the first half stood at 24,664
units as against 27,134 units in the corresponding period last
year, recording a negative growth of 9.8 percent, industry sources
said.
</P>
<P>
While 1,977 Ford Escort cars were sold during the period as
against 4,331 units sold last year, sales figures of General
Motor's Opel Astra stood at 1,973 units as against last year's
5,470 units. South Korean Chaebol Daewoo had a drop of 23.6
percent in the first half at a total sales of 4,213 units of Cielo
car compared with last year's 5,512 units.
</P>
<P>
Honda City car, however, has gathered a market share of 20.6
percent by selling 5,090 cars in the first half of this year.
