<HEADLINE> Report Calls for Prevention of Juvenile Delinquency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Romanian experts Tuesday
urged the government to work out a national strategy on the
prevention of juvenile delinquency which is on the rise in the
country over the last two years.
</P>
<P>
A report of the Romanian Procurator Office's research institute
said the number of juvenile offenders reached 41,898 in 1997, as
against 18,500 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
More than 18,000 young people were detained in 1997 for
stealing and robbery and other offenses include murder and rape,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the juvenile offenders were brought up in
unharmonious families and many came from families where the
parents were unemployed or little educated.
</P>
<P>
The report said a national policy must be worked out
immediately to strengthen the work on youth and children, ensure a
good education for them and encourage them to take an active part
in social activities in efforts to reduce the rate of juvenile
delinquency. 
