<HEADLINE> Fixed Assets Investment Up in Southern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the capital of
China's Guangdong Province, spent 29.7 billion yuan on fixed
assets in the first three quarters of this year, up 15 percent
from the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Key subway, expressway and steelworks projects got 6.7 billion
yuan, 22 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Investment in real estate increased 18 percent. As a result, a
total of 2.61 million sq.m. of housing have been completed, 66
percent more than last year's figure. Over 2 million sq.m. have
been sold.
</P>
<P>
Large investments have helped the city's economy, with the GDP
up 12 percent to 124 billion yuan by the end of September, higher
than the national average. 
