<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Minister Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Communist Party General
Secretary Le Kha Phieu met with Russian Defense Minister Marshal
I.D. Sergeyev Tuesday, official media reports here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev and his high-ranking military delegation arrived here
Tuesday for an official visit to Vietnam at the invitation of his
Vietnamese counterpart Pham Van Tra.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev informed Phieu of the outcome of his earlier talks
with Tra.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev stressed the "similarities between Russia and Vietnam
and the two sides' resolve to further develop their time-honored
friendship and cooperation," the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev promised that Russia will "do its utmost to maintain
and boost bilateral ties for mutual interest."
</P>
<P>
There remains great potential for boosting bilateral
cooperation in economic, commercial, national defense, scientific,
cultural and social domains between Vietnam and Russia, the
Vietnamese party leader noted.
</P>
<P>
According to Russian sources here, during Sergeyev's meeting
with Tra on Tuesday, the Russian side expressed the hope to
maintain its presence in Vietnam's Cam Ranh bay. The two sides
will hold negotiation in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Cam Ranh bay, a former U.S. navy base, was rent to the former
Soviet Union in 1979. After the disintegration of the Soviet
Union, a treaty was signed in 1993 by Vietnam and Russia, allowing
the latter to continue using the Cam Ranh base until 2004.
</P>
<P>
The Russian defense minister is scheduled to leave here
Thursday. 
</P>
