<HEADLINE> China Grabs Two Golds in Weightlifting Worlds for Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 20 (Xinhua) -- China grabbed two golds, two
silvers and two bronzes on the second day of the World
Weightlifting Championships for the Disabled in Dubai, the United
Arab Emirates, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cao Ping improved the world mark by 10 kgs when she lifted 115
kgs to snatch the women's 82.5-kg category gold while Zhu Mingxia
took the women's 60-kg category title at 90 kgs.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Emma Brown smashed the world record in the women's
75-kg category, registering 130 kgs to beat the previous mark of
120 kgs. China's Li Ruifang was second at 110 kgs.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's Zzham Oudra also set the new world mark when she won
the 52-kg category with 102.5 kgs, 12.5 kgs more than the old
mark.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's Zyabo Zsmai La took the women's 48-kg category title
with 95 kgs while another Nigerian won the women's 56-kg category
at 100 kgs. China's Zuo Yu won the 56-kg silver.
</P>
<P>
Egypt was also highly successful in this record-breaking gold
rush when Nadia Mohamed Fakry won the women's 67.5-kg champion
and Faten Hegazy Ahmed took the women's 82.5 kg-above category.
</P>
<P>
Fakry lifted 107.5 kgs to break the previous world record of
92.5 while Faten Hegazy Ahmed hauled 105 kgs to improve on the
old mark of 95 kgs. 
</P>
