<HEADLINE> Chinese Farms Raising Shrimp, Blowfish Together </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The prawn is delicious but
difficult to raise because of its delicate temperament while the
blowfish is a great delicacy for some, especially Japanese, but it
can be extremely poisonous.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in the northern China city of Zhuanghe in Hebei
Province have developed a technique to feed the two together.
</P>
<P>
They have found that breeding the two in the same pond has
helped stop diseases that kill prawn and has given high yields of
blowfish. The excrement of the fish helps to disinfect the prawn
ponds and counter diseases, while the prawn killed by diseases
provide food for the fish.
</P>
<P>
With 6,700 hectares of prawn farms, Zhuanghe has become a major
prawn-cultivating base of the country. Since 1993, Chinese fish
farms have suffered heavy losses because of the spread of
diseases, but many farms in the city have avoided disaster thanks
to the technique.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
