<HEADLINE> Canadian Police Seize 440 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Canadian police have seized 440
kilograms of cocaine hidden in the trunk of a car, according to a
report from Quebec.
</P>
<P>
Quebec provincial police intercepted the vehicle early Tuesday
as it headed west on Highway 132 near Ste-Anne-des-Monts, about
500 kilometres northeast of Quebec City.
</P>
<P>
"It's one of the biggest seizures we've ever had in the Gaspe
region," said Claude Ross, a provincial police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Ross said the cocaine was in small packets. He said he didn't
know the drug's origin or destination.
</P>
<P>
A Montreal-area man in his 30s was arrested. He offered no
resistance when his car was stopped. 
