<HEADLINE> Venezuela's 1999 Revenues Expected to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's 1999 revenues are
expected to drop by 1.1 billion dollars, one percent of its Gross
Domestic Product (GDP), due to falling oil prices, the Venezuelan
central budget office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that the country's real GDP will also decrease next
year.
</P>
<P>
Non-oil sectors will also contract by one percent of GDP,
leading to falling tax revenues, the central budget office said.
</P>
<P>
The country's 1998 estimated oil revenues are expected to show
a 500 million dollar shortfall, the office said.
</P>
<P>
The finance ministry based its budget estimates on a price of
between 12 and 12.5 dollars per barrel next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
