<HEADLINE> Bank Savings Increase In South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Total bank savings in
Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province in south China, stood at
361.36 billion yuan (43.5 billion U.S. dollars) at the end of
September.
</P>
<P>
That included 327.4 billion yuan in the Chinese currency, the
yuan, and foreign currencies worth 4.1 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The savings of local people amounted to 175.25 billion yuan, 21
billion yuan more than the January figure, and company savings of
130.19 billion yuan, up 8.2 billion yuan from January.
</P>
<P>
Bank sources attributed the increase in bank savings to the
housing reform, which ask people to save money for future
house purchases, and to little expectation that there will be price
hikes and a bearish stock market in China. 
</P>
