<HEADLINE> New Crop Strain Gives Central China Province Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province, a leading
grain producer in China, is expected to get 18.5 billion kg of
autumn grain this year, 3.4 percent more than in 1996, an
especially bountiful year.
</P>
<P>
The summer grain output exceeded 20 billion kg and the per
ha. yield rose to 4,800 kg, both all time highs in the
country. Local analysts attributed the good harvest to the use of
of new crop strains in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The province has tried new wheat strains seven times in the
past 50 years and the cycle between each new addition has been
shortened from 7 to 8 years to 3 to 4 years.
</P>
<P>
A new wheat strain developed by local agronomists years
ago has given a per-ha. wheat yield of 3,750 kg. This autumn, the
acreage sown with fine wheat strains grew to 2.6 million ha.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
