<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The International Boxing
Federation (IBF) ordered four highly ranked heavyweight boxers to
fight in a double-box-off to determine a No. 1 mandatory
contender to champion Evander Holyfield Today.
</P>
<P>
No.2 Francois Botha of South Africa will fight No.4 John Ruiz
of the United States, while American No.3 Hasim Rahman will take
on compatriot David Tua, who ranked 12th.
