vacant. Vaughn Bean held the No.1 ranking until he was beaten by
Holyfield on September 19.
</P>
<P>
"I think what the IBF is doing to make you earn the No.1 spot
is terrific and I think the other organizations should follow
suit," said Dino Duva, Tua's promoter.
</P>
<P>
"It's a very good thing, and whoever arrives at No.1 will have
the necessary credulity to be No.1," said Cedric Kushner,
Rahman's promoter.  
