<HEADLINE> Housing Market in North China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 21 (Xinhua) -- Moderately priced residential
housing in Tianjin, the biggest port city in north China, is
doing well, according to local official sources.
</P>
<P>
A record 840 million yuan (about 101 million U.S. dollars)
worth of housing, a total of 260,000 sq.m. of floor space, was sold
during a recent five-day fair.
</P>
<P>
Local people showed unprecedented enthusiasm at the
fair. Business on the opening day broke all real estate fair
records, and on the morning of the closing day, 50,000 sq.m. of
housing was sold.
</P>
<P>
A local housing official attributed the brisk business to the
country's housing policies and the support of public funds and
bank loans.
</P>
<P>
This year is an important year for reshaping the city's old
urban areas, he said. In the first eight months, the local
government allocated 3.4 billion yuan for moving people from old
urban areas and local banks provided 880 million yuan in housing
loans.
</P>
<P>
The strong housing market has helped housing-related industries
and has become a major driving force in the city's economic
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
