<HEADLINE> Fiorentina, Sociedad, Atletico and Lyon Enjoy Away Wins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Fiorentina, Real Sociedad,
Atletico Madrid and Olympique Lyon all enjoyed away wins in the
opening legs of the UEFA Cup second round ties on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Fiorentina, who lost for the first time in the Italian league
when they went down 2-1 to Roma on Sunday, bounced straight back
with a 2-0 win at Grasshoppers in Zurich.
</P>
<P>
Real Sociedad allowed a three-goal lead to slip from their
grasp but still held on to win 3-2 at Dynamo Moscow, while
Olympique Lyon came from a goal behind to beat Crvena Zvezda
Belgrade 2-1 in a match switched by UEFA to neutral Bucharest in
Romania because of the tension in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Atletico Madrid also braved a difficult trip to CSKA Sofia,
winning 4-2 in Bulgaria where two of their goals came from Kiko
Narvaez -- the second coming with almost the last kick of the
game after CSKA had pulled the score back to 2-3 just two minutes
from time.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish club were reduced to 10 men in the 75th minute
when defender Santi was sent off.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in early action, there was a thrilling match in
Austria where Graz AK drew 3-3 with Monaco, with Graz substitute
Anton Ehmann scoring the equalizer deep into time added on for
injury.
</P>
<P>
Bologna won 2-1 at home against Slavia Prague, while fellow
Italians Parma, who won this trophy in 1995, braved a wintry
night in Poland with a 1-1 draw at Wislaw Krakow, a result that
should be enough to earn them a place in the last 16.
</P>
<P>
Club Bruges, playing in the UEFA Cup after early elimination f
rom the European Cup, fought back to draw 1-1 in Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
A total 15 matches were played on Tuesday, with the Bayer
Leverkusen-Rangers game taking place on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
