<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Protecting Forests in Southeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 21 (Xinhua) -- The government of Fujian
province decided recently to tightly control the logging of
forests to protect its environment.
</P>
<P>
Loggers will need to be licensed and restrictions have been
imposed on licensing procedures. Forest station management has
been increased and cases of destruction of forests are being dealt
with forcefully, a provincial government official said.
</P>
<P>
The serious flooding that hit the northern parts of Fujian in
June has been blamed on the province's serious soil erosion
problem and deteriorating environment.
</P>
<P>
The protection program covers forests in scenic spots and
nature reserves, near reservoirs, and in valleys near the upper
reaches of major rivers.
</P>
<P>
Loggings are limited to reafforestation areas, and natural
forests must be reafforested, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
