<HEADLINE> Dow Up 39 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks closed
higher Tuesday amid renewed confidence in the market following the
recent interest cut by the Federal Reserve.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures show that the Dow Jones industrial average
jumped 39.40 points to close at 8,505.85 and broader market
indicators also posed gains.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip barometer soared as high as 186 points in the
early afternoon but it retreated later amid profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
It has so far risen 567 points since last Wednesday, and nearly
1,100 points since late August, but still 832 points below the
record 9,337.97 on July 17.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues led decliners 2-1 with trading volume totaling
947 million shares against 714 million previously on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 1.54 to 1,063.93, but the
technology-linked Nasdaq composite index fell 9.54 to 1,639.19.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 2.78 to 528.28 and the American
Stock Exchange rose 10.55 to 616.27. 
</P>
