<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Progress Made at Mideast Summit in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 20 (Xinhua) -- Israelis and Palestinians
Tuesday began shaping the framework of an agreement on the Israeli
withdrawal from the West Bank on the sixth day of their summit
talks at the Wye Plantation, Maryland.
</P>
<P>
With the joining of U.S. President Bill Clinton and Jordan's
King Hussein, the pace of negotiations picked up Tuesday and both
Israel and the Palestinians got down to hard bargaining.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that while several knotty issues
remained, Israel and the Palestinians had succeeded in reaching a
preliminary understanding on several points.
</P>
<P>
These included a second Israeli pullout from the West Bank in
12 weeks while the Palestinians confiscate illegally weapons and
jail militant terrorists.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. would assume the role of verifying both the weapons
seizure and the jailings, the Associated Press (AP) quoted sources
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli withdrawal from 13 percent of the West Bank and the
Palestinian counterterrorism moves would be carried out in
parallel phases.
</P>
<P>
As the Palestinians demanded a third withdrawal from the West
Bank, the negotiators are examining an Israeli proposal that the
dispute be taken up by an Israeli-Palestinian committee with no
U.S. participation in its deliberations, reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0289 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan: U.S. Failure to Pay Back Dues "Truly Disturbing" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 20 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Tuesday issued a statement through his spokesman's
office, calling the U.S. failure to include funding for U.N.
arrears in anticipated U.S. budget agreement "truly disturbing."
</P>
<P>
"I find this outcome truly disturbing: disturbing for the
United Nations; and disturbing for the standing of the United
States in the United Nations," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"We are at a moment in history when leadership is vital. This
failure by the United States to honor its contract with the rest
of the world does not make that challenge any easier," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The United States needs an effective United Nations, and the
United Nations needs an engaged United States," he said.
"Therefore, we hope the (U.S.) Congress reconvenes (and) the
appropriate compromises will be struck so as to put this mutually
divisive and damaging issue behind us once and for all, enabling
us to get on with the pressing business of serving the world's
people."
</P>
<P>
Annan, who is currently on a visit to Japan, said Monday in
Florida before his departure that the United Nations becomes a
hostage of the U.S. domestic debate on the abortion issue.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the U.S. House of Representatives will
adopt the budget agreement Tuesday night, and the Senate
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the Democrats and Republicans in the U.S.
Congress reached an agreement that would have paid about one
billion U.S. dollars in arrears to the United Nations, beginning
with 475 million U.S. dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the funding was made conditional on a provision
barring U.S. aid to international family planning groups that
lobby countries to liberalize their abortion laws while U.S.
President Clinton said he will veto such a bill.
</P>
<P>
At present, the United States has to pay the United Nations 1.6
billion U.S. dollars in arrears, which accounts for two-thirds of
a total of U.N. outstanding dues.
</P>
<P>
Washington has to pay the United Nations 347 million U.S.
dollars before December 31 this year to avoid "the automatic loss"
of its vote in the General Assembly next year under Article 19 of
the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
A senior U.N. official on Tuesday afternoon told a press
conference here that "we have good information that not a single
penny was contained in the budget bill for U.N. arrears," and "the
possibility for avoiding Article 19 next year is diminishing."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981021.0290 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-21 </DATE_TIME>
