<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council Tuesday expressed concern over the slow progress
in refugee returns throughout the territory of the former
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council was briefed by Mr. Asomani, a U.N official
from the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), on
the situation in the region.
</P>
<P>
The council remained deeply concerned at the slow progress in
refugee returns, especially in and to Bosnia ans Herzegovina and
in eastern Slavonia.
</P>
