<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, October 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus started the annual military exercise
"Nikiforos '98" on Tuesday, with the participation of the Greek
Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reservists who enlisted for the six-day
manoeuvres, Defense Minister Yiannakis Omirou said the National
Guard's annual exercise gives the message that the Cyprus people
firmly support the defense of the island.
</P>
<P>
This, he said, is the main objective of Cyprus and Greece in
the context of the joint defense pact between the two countries,
signed in November 1993. (Cyprus-Military Exercise)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The armed wing of Islamic militant group Hamas
has claimed responsibility for Monday's grenade attack in Israel,
Israel Television reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report added that the arrested suspect is a resident of the
Palestinian-controlled part of the West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Salem Rajab Sarsour, 29, a Palestinian construction worker,
told the interrogators that he also killed a rabbi in Hebron last
month.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Sarsour was admitted into Hamas military
wing only after the killing of Rabbi Shlomo Raanan.
</P>
<P>
Sarsour was arrested after throwing two grenades into a bus
station of the town of Beersheba in Israel's southern Negev
Desert. (Israel-Palestinians-Hamas)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan, the Regent, and
Israeli President Ezer Weizman Tuesday expressed rejection of a
partial agreement at the Palestinian-Israeli summit at the Wye
Plantation near Washington.
</P>
<P>
Jordan rejects "half solutions" and will make efforts to help
both sides achieve a comprehensive agreement over a U.S. peace
proposal which calls for Israel to withdraw from 13.1 percent of
the West Bank, Jordan's official news agency, the Petra, quoted
Hassan as telling Weizman during their telephone conversations.
</P>
<P>
Weizman said that he has been keeping contacts with Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat to ensure that a comprehensive agreement rather than a
partial one will be achieved.
</P>
<P>
Both Hassan and Weizman affirmed that a comprehensive
agreement is necessary because it will bring durable peace to
the region and avoid violence. (Jordan-Israel-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Syria Tuesday pledged to shut down camps of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) on its territory and in the
Syrian-controlled Bekka Valley, Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem said here.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed by high-ranking diplomatic and
military officials of Turkey and Syria, Damascus also agreed not
to allow the PKK militants to launch cross-border attacks on the
Turkish territory, Cem said.
</P>
<P>
Cem's remarks came after high-ranking officials from both
countries ended a two-day secret security meeting held in Turkey's
southern province of Adana. (Turkey-Syria) 
</P>
